{"build_type":"library","description":"Walk the package universe and append, to the output array, the entry function name of every executable package whose call closure reaches the single sanctioned request entry parse-argument-vector-json-request. Libraries and daemons are skipped by kind, and executables that never parse a request (self-contained proofs) are skipped because their closure does not reach the request entry. The result is the derived set of request-taking command tools that the universal output contract and the unknown-parameter rejection contract must hold over. Parameters are packed into ctx to respect the four-parameter cap: slot zero the universe array, one the output target-name array, two the function index; the second parameter is the running index the caller passes as zero. Recurses by index.","module_name":"gather-request-driven-executable-entry-names","package_name":"gather-request-driven-executable-entry-names","function_definitions":{"gather-request-driven-executable-entry-names":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ctx","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"i","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"universe","base":"ctx","index":"zero","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"out","base":"ctx","index":"one","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"index","base":"ctx","index":"two","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation_name":"count-members-inside-container-value","invocation_arguments":[{"kind":"v